shortDescription: Porcini, Bag 1 OZ Fine gourmet dried mushrooms. Recipe inside! 100% natural. Wildcrafted in Nature's Lab - the forest floor. Wild mushrooms - one of nature's miracles! Are full of rich flavor, nutritional goodness, and (some say) healing properties. Their fragrant magic, when preserved by drying, can be enjoyed year round. Simply soak dried mushrooms in warm water (or wine, or stock) for 20-30 minutes, then add to your favorite recipe. Save that soaking liquid and use as a stock or gravy base - it's full of concentrated mushroom flavor! Dried mushrooms keep for months, without refrigeration, and for a year or more if frozen. Delectable fresh or dried, porcini mushrooms are among the most sought-after of all wild-harvest mushrooms. Porcini means little pigs in Italian, so called for their plump floor. In France they are known as cepes; to the Germans they are Steinpilz. With a rich, earthy flavor and heady aroma, porcini may be featured in savory sauces to accompany meat or poultry. Excellent in risottos, omelettes, or served with polenta. Wild harvested. www.earthy.com. Product of China. Always cook mushrooms before eating. May contain naturally occurring sulfites. 1 oz (24.8 g) Okemos, MI 800-367-4709

shortDescription: Pepper Description: The history of this pepper is obscure, but since wild peppers are naturally hot this variety was probably developed over the years among farmers by simple selection of seed from milder and milder fruits. The fruit of aji dulce can be used green or ripe, and it can be seeded and frozen for use over the winter, a technique that also preserves its rich flavor much better than drying. It is a small, light green pepper that turns red if left long enough on the plant. It has the shape and size of a habanero pepper without the intense heat. In the tropics, this plant can grow as a perennial, although most of the commercial production is with annual systems.

name: Tomato, Beefsteak 2.5#
shortDescription: BEEFSTEAK TOMATO: The beefsteak tomato is one of the largest tomato cultivars, with some varieties weighing in at over 2 pounds per tomato. This meaty tomato is grown in a rainbow of colors, from vibrant red to pale yellow to purple-black. Rather than maintaining a perfectly spherical shape as it develops, the beefsteak tomato takes on a decided kidney-bean shape, spreading out to the sides. The beefsteak tomato is one of the slowest-maturing tomatoes, with the largest beefsteak cultivars taking up to 90 days to produce ripe fruit. Typically, the beefsteak tomato vine will continue to produce and set fruit until the first frost. Watermelon Beefsteak Tomato - HEIRLOOM. Pink tomato. 85 days. An amazingly big and meaty beefsteak. Some weigh 2 lbs. and more. The seed cavities are tiny, and the centers are solid with firm, bright red flesh. Very impressive. Pink-skinned tomatoes occur as a result of a clear skin over red flesh. (Ordinary red tomatoes have yellow skin over red flesh.) When ripe fruits retain green pigment, tomatoes take on purple and brownish hues.

shortDescription: Our Favorite tomato! 75 days. Elongated, large cherries in clusters. TOMATO: Tomatoes are rich in vitamins and antioxidants, and the seeds are high in fiber. The green parts are mildly poisonous, which is not surprising, as tomatoes are closely related to both nightshade and tobacco. The tomato was originally believed to be poisonous when introduced into Europe, and was used solely as an ornamental plant during the 16th and 17th centuries. The first traces of its use as a food date back to the first half of the 18th century. Tomatoes are now a tasty ingredient in many dishes, and are used fresh, canned, stewed or even sun-dried.

name: Daikon
shortDescription: Daikon, also called Chinese radish, is an essential ingredient in a wide variety of Asian dishes. The origin of the radish can be traced back to ancient China, but the word Daikon actually comes from two Japanese words: dai (meaning large) and kon (meaning root). As one of the largest radishes, daikon is characterized by its long, narrow appearance and crisp texture. It can range in length from 6 to 15 inches and can average 2 to 3 inches in diameter. The skin is usually white but can also be black. Although it may look similar to a carrot in appearance, its flavor is anything but. It has been described as mildly sweet and juicy with a slightly spicy, peppery bite. This is one versatile Asian vegetable and its fresh flavor is delicious served raw or pickled. It is often used as a condiment, garnish or ingredient in soups, stews, salads and more. Besides enjoying them raw, you can also cook them in many different ways from roasting to steaming and more. They can also be thrown into classic braise with meat, since they absorb their braising liquid beautifully and take on the texture of turnips once cooked. Daikon should be scrubbed with a brush under running water, prior to use. Peel before using or grate with a sharp metal grater
longDescription: Contains: Vitamin C Potassium Phosphorus

shortDescription: Found growing naturally in the wild hidden amongst the forest under bushes and pines, Porcini mushrooms are beloved by chefs, cooks, and food lovers alike. The prized boletus edulis fungi is used in recipes the world over from Italy, France, Spain, and all throughout Asia. The meaty umami-ness of Porcini makes these mushrooms a must have for any mushroom lover. What do Porcini taste like? Often described as meaty, earthy, woody and umami porcini are a favorite in many cuisines. Try for yourself and see what everyone is talking about and enjoy the rich, chewy, nutty and earth flavor profile that makes these mushrooms so darn good. BPA free stand up pouch. In each 100g serving of these Dried Porcini Mushrooms, you're treated to a burst of nutritional goodness. With just 370 calories, they're low in energy while delivering a solid 25g of protein, making them an excellent source for plant-based protein intake. Carbohydrates come in at 68g, including 9g of beneficial fiber, helping to maintain healthy digestion. The total fat content is 3g, with minimal saturated fat at 0.6g, and there's no cholesterol or sodium to worry about. Impressively, these mushrooms offer a substantial 3,700mg of potassium, essential for various bodily functions, along with 100mg of calcium and 3mg of iron, contributing to overall health. Truly a nutritional powerhouse, adding both flavor and wellness to your culinary endeavors. Not only do these mushrooms enhance the taste, but they also bring a wealth of nutrition to your meals. With a low-calorie count, high protein content, and a notable presence of essential minerals like potassium, calcium, and iron, these porcini mushrooms are not just a flavorful choice, but also a wholesome one. Experience the culinary magic of Slofoodgroup's Dried Porcini Mushrooms, a must-have for any food enthusiast looking to elevate their dishes with the finest gourmet ingredients.
longDescription: 2oz Grade A Dried Porcini Mushrooms Our dried porcini are grade A sliced, dried naturally and uniform in thickness. shortDescription: Brussles Sprouts, Bag 12 OZ Steams in pack. Per Serving: 35 calories; 0 g sat fat (0% DV); 20 mg sodium (1% DV); 2 g sugars; vitamin C (120% DV); vitamin K (190% DV). Find Delicious Recipes: GreenGiantFresh.com. Questions or comments? 1-800-998-9996. Follow us on: Facebook and Twitter. Facebook. Twitter. Find delicious recipes, helpful tips & more: Scan code with app; greengiantfresh.com/value-added. Product of USA. Perishable. Keep refrigerated. Microwave in Bag Directions: 1. Pierce bag with fork. 2. Place bag on microwavable plate. 3. Microwave on high for 2-3 minutes. For softer texture, add up to 1 minute. Let sit for 1 minute. Caution: Contents and bag hot! 4. Open bag, pour contents into serving dish and enjoy. Because microwaves vary, cook times are approximate. Saute Directions: 1. Cut 12 oz Brussels Sprouts in half. 2. Heat 2 tbsp olive oil in a skillet on medium-high. Add Brussels Sprouts, 1/2 tsp salt and 1/4 tsp pepper; toss to coat. 3. Pan roast for 8-10 minutes or until nicely browned and tender. 4. name: Dried Mushroom Kibble by Its Delish, 4 Oz Bag Dark Chilean Dehydrated and Chopped Boletus Luteus Mushrooms for Cooking and Flavoring
shortDescription: Dried Kibbled Mushrooms by Its Delish Boletus Luteus mushrooms is a wild-grown dark mushroom with a deep and earthy flavor, commonly called the brown or Chilean mushroom, sorted, washed, trimmed, and air-dried. There are a good source of vitamin, minerals and protein. These are 100% all-natural with no added ingredients or preservatives. These chopped mushroom flakes are used in a wide variety of applications for rich-flavored mushroom for including sauces, gravy, soups, vegetable stock, broth and stews, pasta products, meats and sausages, seasoning blends, salad products, pot pies, and casseroles and ready meals. Prep Instruction Ideas: Add these mushrooms while slow cooking soups, stews, sauces, casseroles and other foods with sufficient liquid content. In other applications, hydrate by using 1 part dried mushroom and 5 parts water. Simmer for 10-15 minutes. Add water if necessary. Yields 1 oz equals about 1/2 cup dry. Generally, air dried vegetables double in volume when hydrated. Dry/Fresh Ratio 1 lb of air dried boletus luteus mushrooms, once rehydrated, equals approximately 6 lbs of fresh prepared boletus luteus mushrooms. Storage Suggestion Best if used within 18 months. Store tightly sealed in a dry location away from sunlight. Tip: For ready to use mushrooms, soak the dry mushrooms in a sealed container and store in the refrigerator. Stock up and enjoy! shortDescription: Dried Kibbled Mushrooms by Its Delish Boletus Luteus mushrooms is a wild-grown dark mushroom with a deep and earthy flavor, commonly called the brown or Chilean mushroom, sorted, washed, trimmed, and air-dried. Prep Instruction Ideas: Add these mushrooms while slow cooking soups, stews, sauces, casseroles and other foods with sufficient liquid content. In other applications, hydrate by using 1 part dried mushroom and 5 parts water. Simmer for 10-15 minutes. Add water if necessary. Yields 1 oz equals about 1/2 cup dry. Generally, air dried vegetables double in volume when hydrated. Dry/Fresh Ratio 1 lb of air dried boletus luteus mushrooms, once rehydrated, equals approximately 6 lbs of fresh prepared boletus luteus mushrooms. Storage Suggestion Best if used within 18 months. Store tightly sealed in a dry location away from sunlight. Tip: For ready to use mushrooms, soak the dry mushrooms in a sealed container and store in the refrigerator. Stock up and enjoy! name: Forest-grown Japanese Dried Shiitake KOSHIN, 42-75mm, 70g
shortDescription: Sugimoto shiitake are naturally cultivated outdoors on special sweet sap oak logs. Moreover, our drying and packaging process keeps the moisture content to less than 9% which enhances the Shiitake flavor and VitaminD content. Sugimoto Shiitake promotes 100% natural and sustainable cultivation using only carefully selected local cultivators. This Shiitake mushroom is called ?Koshin? and is picked after the cap of the Mushroom blooms into an umbrella. It is more large and flat than the ?Donko? Shiitake mushroom which is picked earlier while the cap is still in a bud form. Since Koshin is less thick than the Donko, it is easier and quicker to use requiring less time to rehydrate. Koshin is best used cut and in stir-fries, soups, sauces, where smaller pieces are used with other ingredients. Our products pass a yearly quality audit guaranteeing the consistency of the sourcing and production process of our Dried Shiitake mushroom. This Audit is conducted by the Japanese Ministry of Agriculture, Forestry, and Fisheries with the Japanese Consumers' Co-operative Union. (JCCU)

shortDescription: Dried Kibbled Mushrooms by Its Delish Boletus Luteus mushrooms is a wild-grown dark mushroom with a deep and earthy flavor, commonly called the brown or Chilean mushroom, sorted, washed, trimmed, and air-dried. There are a good source of vitamin, minerals and protein. These are 100% all-natural with no added ingredients or preservatives. These chopped mushroom flakes are used in a wide variety of applications for rich-flavored mushroom for including sauces, gravy, soups, vegetable stock, broth and stews, pasta products, meats and sausages, seasoning blends, salad products, pot pies, and casseroles and ready meals. Prep Instruction Ideas: Add these mushrooms while slow cooking soups, stews, sauces, casseroles and other foods with sufficient liquid content. In other applications, hydrate by using 1 part dried mushroom and 5 parts water. Simmer for 10-15 minutes. Add water if necessary. Yields 1 oz equals about 1/2 cup dry. Generally, air dried vegetables double in volume when hydrated. Dry/Fresh Ratio 1 lb of air dried boletus luteus mushrooms, once rehydrated, equals approximately 6 lbs of fresh prepared boletus luteus mushrooms. Storage Suggestion Best if used within 18 months. Store tightly sealed in a dry location away from sunlight. Tip: For ready to use mushrooms, soak the dry mushrooms in a sealed container and store in the refrigerator. Stock up and enjoy! name: Chayote Squash
shortDescription: Chayote Squash
longDescription: Chayote Squash A member of the gourd family, this versatile produce item from Mexico is quickly becoming a produce department standard. Roughly pear-sized in shape and light apple-green in color, Chayote Squash has a smooth skin with slight ridges running from stem to end. The average Chayote weighs about 1/2 pound and measures approximately 5 inches in length. Though similar to summer squash, Chayote usually requires a longer cooking time because of its firmer texture. Chayote makes a wonderful addition to soups or stir-fries and may be sliced or chopped and used raw like a cucumber. The seeds are also edible. Store Chayote Squash at 45°-50°F. At home, Chayote Squash stays freshest lightly wrapped and refrigerated for up to one week. No need to peel before using.

name: German Butterball Potato - 6 Tubers
shortDescription: Butter-me-not! So versatile -- great for baking, frying, or mashing. 100 days. An heirloom russet with flavor so rich and sweet it would be a crime to smother it in butter, German Butterball is an all-around potato you can rely on as your "main crop" for great year-round eating. You will fall in love with the creamy-sweet flavor even before you appreciate the heavy yields and long storage ability of this favorite! German Butterball sets medium-sized oblong to round russets with yellow flesh, as if they'd already been covered in melted butter. Resistant to disease and scab, these taters look as good as they taste, maturing late in potato season on plants that refuse to be confined to their allotted space, but wander gloriously instead! This plant grows tall, providing great shade protection for the potatoes with large, abundant foliage. Give it plenty of space (because it will take it even if you don't!) and let these flavor-filled roots mature slowly to perfection. You will absolutely love the flavor. German Butterball consistently wins taste tests, but it's also quite versatile, as happy being mashed as it is fried, baked, or boiled. Rely on it for homegrown potato goodness!

These chopped mushroom flakes are used in a wide variety of applications for rich-flavored mushroom for including sauces, gravy, soups, vegetable stock, broth and stews, pasta products, meats and sausages, seasoning blends, salad products, pot pies, and casseroles and ready meals. Prep Instruction Ideas: Add these mushrooms while slow cooking soups, stews, sauces, casseroles and other foods with sufficient liquid content. In other applications, hydrate by using 1 part dried mushroom and 5 parts water. Simmer for 10-15 minutes. Add water if necessary. Yields 1 oz equals about 1/2 cup dry. Generally, air dried vegetables double in volume when hydrated. Dry/Fresh Ratio 1 lb of air dried boletus luteus mushrooms, once rehydrated, equals approximately 6 lbs of fresh prepared boletus luteus mushrooms. Storage Suggestion Best if used within 18 months. Store tightly sealed in a dry location away from sunlight. Tip: For ready to use mushrooms, soak the dry mushrooms in a sealed container and store in the refrigerator. Stock up and enjoy! shortDescription: Ginger Root, this extremely versatile root is known for its popularity in Asian and Indian cooking. The Chinese, Japanese, and East Indians use Ginger Root in many forms by grating or grinding them. Fresh Ginger is available in two forms; Young Ginger and Mature Ginger. Young Ginger is very tender and has a milder flavor than its mature counterpart, which has a tough skin that preserves a peppery, slightly sweet-hot flesh underneath. Grown in Jamaica, India, Africa, and China, Ginger is a gnarled and knobby root that has a brown, dry skin and a pale yellow to ivory flesh. Ginger Root serves a variety of usages and is utilized to make confections, baked goods, and even certain liqueurs. Ginger is the flavor of popular beverages like Ginger Ale and Ginger Beer. It is delicious in many savory dishes such as soups, curries, and meats and is indispensable in the making of sweets such as Gingerbread, Gingersnaps, and many spice cookies.

name: Mushroom Lion's Mane 4 oz
shortDescription: Caputo & Guest Lion’s Mane Mushrooms are among the most distinctive and intriguing gourmet mushrooms, celebrated for their remarkable flavor, nutrition, and appearance. Grown with care by America’s leading domestic grower of exotic mushrooms, these ivory-white clusters feature cascading, icicle-like spines that resemble a lion’s mane—earning their memorable name. With a firm, meaty texture and a delicate, seafood-like flavor often compared to lobster or crab, Lion’s Mane offers a naturally rich, savory taste that enhances both plant-based and protein-forward recipes. Their consistent quality and freshness make them a signature of Caputo & Guest’s chef-inspired collection. Cultivated in Kennett Square, Pennsylvania—the Mushroom Capital of the World—Caputo & Guest’s Lion’s Mane mushrooms are grown on a proprietary, upcycled hardwood sawdust blend that mirrors their natural forest habitat. This sustainable, manure-free substrate supports steady growth, purity, and superior flavor, producing dense, firm mushrooms bursting with umami. Each cluster is hand-harvested at peak maturity, trimmed, and packed to preserve its delicate structure and freshness. The result is a premium ingredient trusted by chefs, wellness enthusiasts, and home cooks alike. When cooked, Lion’s Mane mushrooms develop a golden, lightly crisp exterior with a tender, seafood-like bite and subtle sweetness. Their natural ability to absorb flavors makes them ideal for grilling, sautéing, roasting, or pan-searing. They pair beautifully with butter, olive oil, garlic, miso, soy, and citrus—transforming simple recipes into elevated, restaurant-quality dishes. Whether used as a satisfying meat substitute or as a complement to seafood and pasta, Lion’s Mane delivers refined flavor and texture that fit seamlessly into modern, health-driven cuisine. Nutritionally, Lion’s Mane is a powerhouse of plant-based wellness. Low in calories and fat-free, it’s rich in dietary fiber, protein, and antioxidants. Naturally occurring compounds such as hericenones and erinacines may support cognitive health and memory by stimulating nerve growth factor (NGF). Lion’s Mane also provides potassium, iron, zinc, and essential amino acids—making it a valuable ingredient for consumers seeking nutrient-dense, functional foods. With growing awareness of brain health and “smart foods,” Lion’s Mane has become a star in the gourmet produce category. Caputo & Guest’s growing practices emphasize sustainability, transparency, and quality. By cultivating Lion’s Mane domestically under precisely controlled indoor conditions, the company ensures a consistent, year-round supply while reducing reliance on imports. This local production model shortens the supply chain, lowers carbon footprint, and delivers fresher, better-tasting mushrooms nationwide. Each harvest is carefully monitored for purity, safety, and consistency—upholding the brand’s reputation for excellence. Marketing highlights: • Naturally Brain-Boosting & Cognitive Supportive • Sustainably Grown in the USA • Manure-Free Hardwood Substrate • Excellent Source of Plant-Based Protein & Fiber • Rich, Lobster-Like Flavor • No Artificial Additives or Preservatives Their striking appearance and culinary versatility make Lion’s Mane mushrooms a standout in premium produce, natural foods, and wellness-focused grocery sections. They embody the modern intersection of taste and function—appealing to chefs, retailers, and health-conscious consumers alike.
longDescription: Gourmet mushroom blend: contains Maitake, King Oyster, and Pearl Oyster. Organic certification. Grown without manure. Locally produced in the U.S.

shortDescription: Upton's Naturals Fava Bean Taco Style Crumbles have a mouthwatering texture & a unique flavor that completes any Mexican-style dish, pasta, or veggies. Key Information 100% vegan meat alternative 9g of protein per serving Low-calorie and no added sugars Low in fat and cholesterol-free Kosher, gluten-free, and non-GMO Product Overview Upton's Naturals is a plant-based food company that launched Fava Bean Taco Style Crumbles,one of the first plant-based fillings made from fava beans.Chicago-based, they explore alternative proteins that are as nutritious as they are delicious! They are widely known as broad beans – one of the oldest known cultivated crops in the world. Fava beans are becoming increasingly popular because of their high nutrition, lack of allergens, and sustainability qualities. shortDescription: Freshly peeled tomatillos are small, firm, and green, making them an essential ingredient in Mexican and Latin American cuisine. This flavor profile allows them to cut through the richness of many dishes, providing a natural brightness that enhances culinary creations. Ideal for making thick sauces and salsas, peeled tomatillos are a kitchen staple for adding zest to your recipes.

name: Finca AR - Recao -Culantro, 6oz
shortDescription: The Recao from AR Farm Finca AR is incredible! It is a very popular aromatic herb in Caribbean cuisine. Although it has an aroma similar to cilantro, its flavor is a little more intense and earthy. Recao is widely used as a seasoning in a variety of dishes, from stews and soups to rice dishes and marinades. It is a fundamental ingredient in the preparation of the famous sofrito, an aromatic mixture of vegetables and herbs that is used as a base in many Caribbean recipes. One of the most interesting characteristics of recao is its ability to retain its flavor even after being cooked at high temperatures, making it ideal for dishes that require long cooking times.
longDescription: Recao is a versatile and delicious herb that adds unique flavor to a wide range of Caribbean dishes. Recao also has medicinal properties (e.g., treating colds, inflammation, digestive issues) Its flavor is more intense and earthy. Long, serrated green leaves Strong, pungent aroma Flavor similar to cilantro but more intense. Common ingredient in sofrito and seasoning bases. Grows well in warm, humid climates. Often grown in home gardens in tropical regions.

shortDescription: Village Farms Greenhouse Grown Premium Lip Smackn' Grape Tomatoes are healthy and nutritious. Poppin' Fresh Flavor for Happy Taste buds! Bit-sized tomatoes with big juicy flavor. Naturally low in calories and excellent source of vitamin C. Splendid for snacking or salads, perfect for school lunches, or as a nutritious treat anytime. The ways to enjoy these miniature tomatoes are countless. Nutritious snacking as an excellent source of vitamin C & beta-carotene which is a natural immune booster. Do not refrigerate for best flavor. leave a bowl on the counter with these snack sized tomatoes for healthy easy snacking. Try this tasty cooked guajillo salsa recipe using 2lb of grape tomatoes. Start by charring whole white onion, 1 red sweet bell pepper and 1 jalapeno and 4 garlic cloves for 10 min. Then char half the grape tomatoes along with a few green onions. Cut all into small pieces and add to a blender along with ancho chilis (rehydrate in bowl of hot water if using dried). Then add all the blended veggies to a pot and simmer until reduced by half. Let cool, add 2.5tbsp red wine vinegar and 2 tbsp olive oil and whisk until blended. Next, blister remaining 1lb grape tomatoes in hot pan. Fold together with simmered veggies for your salsa mixture. Lip Smackn' Grape tomatoes are perfect for cooking, grilling or roasting. Lip Smackn' Grape tomatoes are perfect for eating raw and fresh. Always store at room temperature for maximum flavor. Keep a bowl of Lip Smackn' Grape tomatoes on the kitchen counter for quick and healthy snacking or spontaneous snack attacks. Lip Smackn' Grape tomatoes make a wonderful fresh salsa by mixing together well 1 cup fresh corn, 1 diced green bell pepper, 4 green onions diced, 1 tbsp chopped parsley. 2 tbsp lemon juice, and 1.5 tsp cajun seasoning. Lip Smackn' Grape tomato salsa is great over roasted salmon.

name: Prico Red Onion Slice
shortDescription: Prico Red onion slices can be cut into half-moons for salads and sandwiches, or into full rings for burgers and fried onion rings. The slicing method depends on your recipe and whether you want the onions to hold their shape or soften easily. Red onions are small to medium in size, averaging 10-15 centimeters in diameter, and are round to slightly oval in shape. The bulb is wrapped in red-purple thin, papery, parchment-like skin that is delicate and easily flakes off when touched. Underneath the skin, there is a burgundy wine-colored sheath that protects the flesh, and the dark purple flesh is firm, crisp, and coarse with many layers of white and purple rings. Red onions are crunchy, pungent, sweet, and slightly spicy when raw and when cooked their flavor lessens and grows mildly sweeter. The intensity of the pungent flavor varies depending on age, particular variety, and the amount of sulfur in the growing soil or the fertilizer used.
longDescription: Fresh Vegetables Quick to prepare Finely chopped Saves time

name: Prico Green diced Bell Pepper
shortDescription: Prico Green bell peppers are unripe bell peppers, which is why they have a slightly bitter, grassy flavor and are less sweet than their fully ripened red, yellow, and orange counterparts. They are nutritious, rich in vitamin C and B6, and can be eaten raw or cooked in dishes like stir-fries, fajitas, or roasted and stuffed. Green bell peppers are an excellent source of vitamin C and B6. A cup of chopped green bell pepper provides a good amount of fiber and is relatively low in carbohydrates. Green bell peppers are often less expensive than red, yellow, and orange ones due to being in an earlier stage of their growth cycle.
longDescription: Fresh Vegetables Quick to prepare Use in a variety of recipes

name: Prico Diced tricolor Bell Pepers
shortDescription: Prico Chopped tricolor bell peppers are versatile and can be added to a variety of dishes, such as being sautéed for a side dish, tossed into salads, or used as a filling for stuffed peppers. To prepare them, wash, core, and chop the peppers into desired shapes, then cook them as part of a larger recipe or enjoy them raw. Chopped tricolor bell peppers are a versatile ingredient, adding vibrant color and mild, sweet flavor to a variety of dishes. They are available pre-diced for convenience or can be prepared from fresh red, yellow, and orange (or green) bell peppers.
longDescription: Fresh Vegetables Quick to prepare Finely chopped Saves time

name: Prico Red Bell Peper diced
shortDescription: A red bell pepper is a mature, sweet, and non-spicy pepper with a crisp texture, technically a fruit but used as a vegetable. It is a good source of vitamins A and C, antioxidants, and can be eaten raw or cooked in various dishes. It is simply a green bell pepper that has been left to ripen. Contains antioxidants like beta-cryptoxanthin and anthocyanins, which may protect against cell damage and support brain health. A nutrient-dense food with no fat and low calories. Includes lutein and zeaxanthin, which may help protect the retina from oxidative damage and reduce the risk of cataracts and macular degeneration.
longDescription: Fresh Vegetables Quick to prepare Saves time

name: Prico Sliced Yellow Onion
shortDescription: Prico Slice yellow onion, cut off the stem end, peel it, then slice it in half lengthwise through the root end. Lay one half flat and slice it crosswise from top to bottom, and repeat with the other half to get two sets of slices. his is the most common method and is great for salads, sandwiches, and recipes where the onion's texture is a key feature.
longDescription: Fresh Vegetables Quick to prepare Finely chopped Saves time

name: Prico Yellow Pepper diced
shortDescription: • Yellow bell peppers are a sweet, non-spicy variety of pepper that is rich in vitamins A and C and antioxidants. They have a crisp texture and can be eaten raw or cooked in dishes like salads, stir-fries, and stuffed peppers, adding a vibrant color and mild, sweet flavor. Yellow bell peppers are a versatile and healthy ingredient, suitable for a wide range of culinary uses. They are an excellent source of vitamins A and C, and contain antioxidants like carotenoids and polyphenols. Dice them for salads, slice them for a crunchy snack, or add them to sandwiches and salsas. Yellow bell peppers are known for their mild, sweet flavor, which is sweeter than green bell peppers.
longDescription: Fresh Vegetables Quick to prepare Saves time

name: Prico Red Onion diced
shortDescription: Prico red onion diced is a type of onion cultivar known for its distinctive purplish-red skin and white flesh with red tinges. They are typically medium to large in size and prized for their relatively mild, sweet, and slightly spicy flavor compared to white or yellow onions, making them ideal for a variety of culinary uses, especially when raw. To dice a red onion, cut off the top, slice it in half, and peel it. Then, make vertical cuts on each half, stopping before the root end, followed by two horizontal cuts. Finally, cut across the first cuts to create small, uniform pieces.
longDescription: Fresh Vegetables Quick to prepare Finely chopped Saves time

name: Prico Dice Yellow Onion
shortDescription: The yellow onion or brown onion is a variety of dry onions with a strong flavor. It is yellow-white inside, with a brown papery exterior. The yellow onion is higher in sulfur content than the white onion, which gives it a stronger, more complex flavor. The yellow onion is the most common and versatile onion variety, known as an all-purpose cooking onion. It has brown, papery skin and white-to-cream-colored flesh. They are the "workhorse" of the onion family and an excellent base for building flavor in a wide variety of cooked dishes. They are rich in flavonoids, particularly quercetin, which have antioxidants and anti-inflammatory properties and may help reduce the risk of chronic diseases. Yellow onions contain significantly more antioxidants than white onions.
